==English==
===Etymology===
From Inuktitut, litteraly "in the linkness of a human" (plural ''inuksuit'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#(Canadian)a stone piling, or [[carin]] that represents a humanoid figure, and was traditionally constructed by people of the [[Inuit]] tribes.

#: ''The symbol of the Vancouver 2010 Olympics in an inukshuk.''

